\vspace{2cm}
\begin{center}
{\bf Abstract}
\end{center}
{\small We present new supersymmetric domain wall and string solutions
of five-dimensional $N = 2$ gauged supergravity coupled to an
arbitrary number of vector multiplets. Using the techniques of very
special geometry allows to obtain the most general domain wall
preserving half of the supersymmetries. This solution, which describes a
renormalization group flow in the dual field theory, is given in terms of
Weierstrass elliptic functions. The magnetically charged, one quarter
supersymmetric string solutions are shown to be closely related to Liouville
theory. We furthermore investigate general product space compactifications,
and show that topological transitions from AdS$_3$ $\times$ S$^2$ to
AdS$_3$ $\times$ H$^2$ can occur when one moves in moduli space.
}

